Response made with JRG: JRG: This could be an option in the browser, but an author or authoring tool could use just look at the title in the header of a URL (either electronically or with a browser) and insert the title text in the TITLE attribute of the ANCHOR element. 
People were discussing simple usage strategies for TITLE, ALT and LONGDESC. 
This seemed to be one option that I thought would be good for the TITLE attribute. 
